<p>I hear you, Aaron. The clarity of the world immediately after I upgrade my glasses prescription always astounds me, and the first one was a huge shock.</p>

<p>I was in a similar position as you, and I didn&#8217;t get glasses for years until after I needed them, but I <em>really</em> liked the impressionistic effect of being partially blind and seeing everything in blur. I&#8217;ve worn glasses now for about 10 years, but I still like to walk around without them on sometimes and experience the world in blurs and soft edges, without the extraneous details and the hard, sharp boundaries of the objects of the world.</p>

