<div id="c11">
<p>You should consider LASIK, it&#8217;s one of the best things I&#8217;ve done. I loved contacts, but it&#8217;s nice to have perfect eyesight all the time. You lose the morning / evening ritual, and if you live your life with very irregular hours like me, your contacts won&#8217;t get uncomfortable after wearing them 16 hours.</p>

<p>Besides, it&#8217;s one of the more surreal experiences you can have - you&#8217;re awake, with eyes wide open. High precision machinery swoops down on your eye, peels your cornea away, and attacks it with beepy lasers. You can see your field of vision getting clearer bit by bit. To some, that sounds like the worse thing ever, but I got a kick out of it.</p>

